Emission factor exploratory data analysis

2022-07-22

This Markdown explores the FAOmassbalance and Edgar Food data and calculates emission factors based on this data.

Do the basic data setup in below code chunk.

library(mrcommons)
library(magrittr)
library(tidyverse)
library(rworldmap)

foodEmi <- readSource("EDGARfood", subtype="foodSystemSector")

foodBal <- calcOutput("FAOmassbalance", aggregate = F)

foodEmi <- toolCountryFill(foodEmi)

foodBal <- time_interpolate(foodBal, seq(1990,2018) )

In FAOmassbalance some years are missing, these are interpolated or extrapolated. In EDGARFood some countries are missing or not according to the current iso standart. This will result in NAs when calculating emission factors.

Production

Description

The emission factors for the production emissions are calculated each year (y) for each country (c). \[emissionFactorProd_{~c~y}=\frac{productionEmissions_{~c~y}}{nrProduction_{~c~y}} \] productionEmissions is the EDGARfood data on the emissions of the production stage in the life-cycle of food products. It is composed of emissions from the agricultural land (fertilisation, drainage of soils, waste burning etc. ) as well as from the production of chemicals and solvents that are used for agricultural purposes (fertilizer, plastic, pesticides etc.) (Crippa,M et al p. 205-206). All GHG substances (CO_2 , CH_4 , N_2O, fluorinated gases; all in kt co2eq) are summed. The unit is converted to mt co2eq.

nrProduction is the FAOmassbalance data on reactive nitrogen (nr) production of the food system of each country.

The calculations are carried out below.

# prepare the source data
emiFacProd <- 
  mbind(dimSums(foodEmi[,,"Production"], "Substance")*(10^-3),      # productionEmission
        # take emssions form all substances combined
        dimSums(foodBal[,,"production.nr"], dim= "ItemCodeItem")%>% # nrProduction 
            collapseDim( dim=3.1) 
        # take nr production output of all items combined

       )

getItems(emiFacProd, dim=3) <- c("emissions", "nrproduction")

# calculate the emission factor
Fac <- ifelse( emiFacProd[,,"nrproduction"]>0, emiFacProd[,,"emissions"]/ emiFacProd[,,"nrproduction"], NaN)

getItems(Fac, dim=3) <- c("emissionFactorProd")

emiFacProd <- mbind(emiFacProd, Fac)

NAs

Check how many NAs are introduced in 2010

cat("Total NAs introduced: ")
## Total NAs introduced:
emiFacProd[,"y2010","emissionFactorProd"] %>% is.na %>% sum() %>% cat(.,"\n")
## 64
cat("Number of cuntries where emissions is NA: ")
## Number of cuntries where emissions is NA:
emiFacProd[,"y2010","emissions"] %>% is.na %>% sum() %>% cat(.,"\n")
## 30
cat("Number of cuntries where nrproduction is zero: ")
## Number of cuntries where nrproduction is zero:
(emiFacProd[,"y2010","nrproduction"]==0) %>% sum() %>% cat(.,"\n")
## 60

Plots

Plot the emission factors to get a quick spatial overview. In order to get the high values into the picture but capture display variance in the low values a log scaling for the colors is used.

{m <- luplot::plotcountrymap(emiFacProd[,"y1990","emissionFactorProd"], catMethod="logFixedWidth",  missingCountryCol = "gray", addLegend=FALSE)
do.call( addMapLegend, c( m
                          , legendLabels="all"
                          , legendWidth=0.5
))}

Processing

Description

The emission factor is calculated each year (y) for each country (c). \[emissionFactorProcc_{~c~y}=\frac{processingEmissions_{~c~y}}{nrProcessing_{~c~y}} \] processingEmissions is the EDGARfood data on the emissions of the processing stage in the life-cycle of food products. This includes the emissions from combustion in the food and tobacco processing industry. (Crippa, M et al p. 206) All GHG substances (CO_2 , CH_4 , N_2O, fluorinated gases; all in kt co2eq) are summed. The unit is converted to mt co2eq.

nrProcessing is based on the FAOmassbalance data on nr output of different processing economies of each country.

# prepare the source data
emiFacProcc <- 
  mbind(dimSums(foodEmi[,,"Processing"], "Substance")*(10^-3), #processingEmissions
        dimSums(foodBal[,, 
                        c("food", "milling", "refining" ,
                          "extracting" , "fermentation", 
                          "distilling") ][,,"nr"], 
                dim= c("ItemCodeItem", "ElementShort") ) #nrProcessing
       )

getItems(emiFacProcc, dim=3) <- c("emissions", "nrprocessing")

# calculate the emission factor
Fac <- ifelse( emiFacProcc[,,"nrprocessing"]>0, emiFacProcc[,,"emissions"]/ emiFacProcc[,,"nrprocessing"], NaN)

getItems(Fac, dim=3) <- c("emissionFactorProcc")

emiFacProcc <- mbind(emiFacProcc, Fac)
